text: Pasiphilodes testulata, the pome looper, is a moth of the family Geometridae. The species was first described by Achille Guenée in 1857. It is found in Tasmania and on Norfolk Island, as well as in New Zealand and on the Chatham Islands and Kermadec Islands. ==Subspecies== *Pasiphilodes testulata testulata *Pasiphilodes testulata nobbsi (Holloway, 1977) ==References== Category:Moths described in 1857 Category:Eupitheciini Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Moths of Australia Category:Arthropods of Tasmania Category:Fauna of Norfolk Island
